Demo Steps:

  • To start, we will download data needed for the lab from Demo Data. Following the download, we will unzip the data and point our GIS to the data and secure a file path for the duration of the lab. Data download includes:

    • ManPLUTO.shp
    • man_centroid.shp
    • man_build.shp

  • Inside the working folder, create a new folder called exports that will hold export .shps developed during this lab.

  • Step 1 - Geoprocessing - Buffer (1 mile Central Park Centroid):

    • IMPORT man_centroid.shp to TOC (table of contents)
    • BUFFER man_centroid.shp - 1 mile distance buffer. Name output cen_buff.shp
    • EXPORT cen_buff.shp to scratch folder (exports)

  • Step 2 - Geoprocessing - Clip #1 (Pluto Parcels):

    • IMPORT ManPLUTO.shp
    • CLIP ManPLUTO.shp - Clip layer = cen_buff.shp. Name output manPLUTO_clip.shp
    • EXPORT manPLUTO_clip.shp to scratch folder (exports)

  • Step 3 - Geoprocessing - Clip #2 (NYC Buildings Footprint):

    • IMPORT man_build.shp
    • CLIP man_build.shp - Clip layer = cen_buff.shp. Name output manbuild_clip.shp
    • EXPORT manbuild_clip.shp to scratch folder (exports)

  • Step 4 - Geoprocessing - Union (Buildings Footprint + Pluto):

    • UNION manbuild_clip.shp + manPLUTO_clip.shp. Name output man_union.shp
    • EXPORT man_union.shp to scratch folder (exports)
    • Visually REVIEW attribute table of man_union.shp

  • Step 5 - Geoprocessing - Intersect (Buildings Footprint + Pluto):

    • INTERSECT manbuild_clip.shp + manPLUTO_clip.shp. Name output man_intersect.shp
    • EXPORT man_intersect.shp to scratch folder (exports)
    • Visually REVIEW attribute table of man_intersect.shp

  • Step 6 - Geoprocessing - DISSOLVE (Intersect results from step 5):

    • DISSOLVE man_intersect.shp. Name output man_dissolve.shp
    • EXPORT man_dissolve.shp to scratch folder (exports)
    • Visually REVIEW attribute table of man_dissolve.shp

  • Step 7 - Calculate Feature Geometry (Pluto Parcels):

    • ADD FIELD TO manPLUTO_clip.shp, Column Type = FLOAT; Name = A_METER
    • CALCULATE GEOMETRY Tool within new A_METER column; Units = Sq. Meter

  • Step 8 - Assign Values | Weights (Pluto Parcels):

    • ADD FIELD TO manPLUTO_clip.shp, Column Type = Text; Name = A_VALUE
    • ASSIGN qualitative values in A_VALUE for area quantities in A_METER
      • SQL Following within A_METER:
      • A_METER<=200 - Assign value small within A_Value
      • A_METER>=200 and A_METER<=3000 - assign medium in A_VALUE
      • A_METER>=3000 - Assign value Large within A_Value

  • Step 9 - Thematically Map | Parcel Sizes S/M/L (Pluto Parcels):

    • THEMATICALLY MAP A_VALUE via categories, unique values (Qualitative)
